Summary:
- Created complete InternPay application in app/page.tsx
- Implements all PRD specifications for UI/UX
- Three-screen state management: assessment, loading, verdict
- Dark theme with deep charcoal (#1A1A1A) and amber (#F59E0B) accents
- Integration with Pay Assessment Manager agent (ID: 6985af5c2a763ad393eee3ed)
- TypeScript interfaces built from actual test response data

Features Implemented:
1. Assessment Screen:
   - Role dropdown (10 options)
   - Skills multi-select (Enter to add, removable tags)
   - Hours/week slider (10-60+)
   - Company type selector (Startup, MNC, Agency, NGO)
   - City dropdown with tier indication (10 cities)
   - Current stipend input with INR validation
   - Duration selector (1-12 months)
   - Form validation and error handling

2. Verdict Screen:
   - Large verdict badge (Fair/Underpaid/Exploited) with color coding
   - Stipend comparison card showing current vs fair range
   - Industry averages panel with source citation
   - Negotiation coaching with 4 expandable scenarios
   - Key talking points list
   - Anonymous intern stories (top 3 by relevance)
   - Next steps guidance
   - Legal disclaimer footer

3. Message Drafting Panel:
   - Right slide-over (Sheet component)
   - Tone selector (professional, firm, casual)
   - Editable textarea with pre-drafted messages
   - Key points checklist
   - Copy to clipboard functionality
   - Dos and Don'ts guidance
   - Timing advice

4. Safety Features:
   - Extreme case detection
   - Safety modal with resources and helpline information
   - Alert system for critical situations

5. Technical Implementation:
   - Uses callAIAgent from lib/aiAgent.ts
   - Uses copyToClipboard from lib/clipboard.ts
   - All icons from lucide-react (no react-icons)
   - No toast/sonner notifications
   - Proper state preservation in form inputs
   - TypeScript interfaces matching actual agent response structure

